c model. The neutron star acts as the\nperturbing body, truncating and distorting the disc. The first outburst would\noccur before the disc is strongly perturbed. The second outburst leads to the\ndispersal of the disc and marks the end of the perturbed phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Nov 2006 11:01:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
